## 3. Data Flow Design

### 3.1 Data Structures

#### 3.1.1 Equipment Interface
```typescript
interface Equipment {
  id: string;
  type: string;
  typeName: string;
  brand: string;
  brandId: string;
  model: string;
  modelId: string;
  yearRange?: string;
  compatibilityId: string;
  systems: string[];
}
```

#### 3.1.2 Part Interface
```typescript
interface Part {
  _id: string;
  name: string;
  sku: string;
  brand: string;
  category: string;
  price: number;
  image: string;
  description: string;
  specs: Record<string, string>;
  compatibility: string[];
  inStock: boolean;
  stock: number;
  rating: number;
  reviews: number;
  oemCode: string;
  compatibilityScore: number;
  compatibilityStatus: 'compatible' | 'incompatible' | 'unknown';
}
```

#### 3.1.3 Compatibility Matrix
```typescript
interface CompatibilityMatrix {
  [partId: string]: {
    equipmentId: string;
    compatibilityScore: number;
    compatibilityReasons: string[];
    compatibilityStatus: 'compatible' | 'incompatible' | 'unknown';
  };
}
```

### 3.2 Data Fetching Strategy

#### 3.2.1 API Endpoints
```typescript
// Fetch compatible parts for specific equipment
GET /api/parts/compatible?equipmentId={equipmentId}&filters={filters}

// Get compatibility information for specific part
GET /api/parts/{partId}/compatibility?equipmentId={equipmentId}

// Batch compatibility check
POST /api/parts/compatibility/check
{
  equipmentId: string;
  partIds: string[];
}
```

#### 3.2.2 Caching Strategy
- **Equipment Data**: Cached in localStorage with TTL
- **Compatibility Matrix**: Server-side caching with Redis
- **Part Data**: Incremental updates with cache invalidation

### 3.3 Compatibility Matching Logic

#### 3.3.1 Compatibility Scoring Algorithm
```typescript
function calculateCompatibilityScore(
  part: Part,
  equipment: Equipment,
  equipmentDatabase: EquipmentDatabase
): number {
  const baseScore = 50;
  
  // Brand match bonus
  const brandBonus = part.brand === equipment.brand ? 20 : 0;
  
  // Category match bonus
  const categoryBonus = part.category === equipment.type ? 15 : 0;
  
  // Direct compatibility match
  const directMatch = part.compatibility.includes(equipment.compatibilityId) ? 30 : 0;
  
  // System compatibility check
  const systemCompatibility = calculateSystemCompatibility(part, equipment, equipmentDatabase);
  
  return baseScore + brandBonus + categoryBonus + directMatch + systemCompatibility;
}
```

#### 3.3.2 System Compatibility Check
```typescript
function calculateSystemCompatibility(
  part: Part,
  equipment: Equipment,
  equipmentDatabase: EquipmentDatabase
): number {
  const compatibleSystems = equipmentDatabase.systems.filter(system => 
    part.compatibility.some(comp => 
      equipmentDatabase[system].includes(comp)
    )
  );
  
  return compatibleSystems.length * 5; // 5 points per compatible system
}
```

